    <note>Wu(3) Kui [8162] His ancestors lived in Jinan, Yucheng xian. During the disorder of the Five Dynasties, at some unknown generation, the family moved to Weizhou, Beihai xian. None of his patrilineal ancestors of the previous three generations held office. His mother's father Wang(2) Ting(2) [3981], a Weizhou, Beihai resident, attempted to pass the mingjing exam and failed. He later became the prefectural teacher (zhujiao). The father of his first wife, Zhao(1) Li [3204], was a county magistrate, from a wealthy Jizhou, Xindu xian family. When Kui was twenty, he had already gained a reputation as a classical scholar and Zhao(1) Li made him his son-in-law despite the fact that the Wu(3) family was considered to be quite poor. Zhao(1) Shi was Jing's [1963] mother. His second wife's father, Zhang(1) Yu(2) [3176], had a nominal title. Liu Ban, WJ, 37.1a-7b; Liu Chang, WJ, 53.17b-19a (wife #1, born Zhao, who married him at age 20 and died in 1039 at age 32); Ouyang Xiu, WJ, 36.6a (mother, see documentation for father, Huaide [22339]). CBD, 2, 1095-6.</note>
